36:30.285 --> 36:33.688
How was your first day?

36:34.164 --> 36:35.931
It was fine.

37:25.892 --> 37:28.452
Baba used to let me
listen to his heartbeat.

37:28.477 --> 37:31.345
It always helped me fall asleep.

37:42.453 --> 37:45.517
How was your first day, really?

37:51.320 --> 37:52.837
I loved it.

38:50.003 --> 38:52.704
Ah, you're supposed to find
Bishop before changing.

38:52.853 --> 38:55.667
Don't apologize, he hates that.

39:02.011 --> 39:04.908
You wanted to see me, sir?

39:06.179 --> 39:07.986
The Blakemore.

39:08.234 --> 39:10.640
It better not have been the first
time you pulled that move.

39:14.328 --> 39:17.062
Dr. Leblanc thinks you
saved that man's life.

39:17.439 --> 39:19.190
You could just as
easily have killed him.

39:19.215 --> 39:21.609
Most emergent Blakemores
end in the morgue.

39:26.675 --> 39:29.369
I did say to find your place, here.

39:33.203 --> 39:34.703
Dr. Bishop?

39:36.451 --> 39:39.072
I've been asked to provide
the original copies

39:39.097 --> 39:40.764
of my medical school transcripts.

39:40.789 --> 39:42.523
But I need you to know

39:42.548 --> 39:45.103
my university might never release them.

39:45.768 --> 39:47.182
But sir, I did earn my degree.

39:47.207 --> 39:49.627
I am the doctor I told you I was.

39:53.670 --> 39:55.564
Close the door on your way out.

40:04.931 --> 40:06.528
We were able to confirm

40:06.553 --> 40:08.584
that the toxin you and
your wife ingested

40:08.609 --> 40:10.224
came from wild mushrooms.

40:10.249 --> 40:11.920
I picked those mushrooms.

40:11.945 --> 40:13.362
This was all my fault.

40:13.387 --> 40:15.131
Well, you're both responding
to treatment well.

40:15.156 --> 40:17.423
- It will take some time, but...
- Maybe...

40:18.531 --> 40:20.302
they were right to judge me.

40:20.327 --> 40:21.452
No they weren't.

40:21.477 --> 40:23.101
People can think what
they want to think,

40:23.126 --> 40:24.679
but you know who you are.

40:24.761 --> 40:26.248
A man who loves his family.

40:27.738 --> 40:29.287
Daddy!

40:29.792 --> 40:33.381
Hey. There's my brave girl.

40:34.942 --> 40:37.459
- Hey, baby.
- Hi.

40:39.737 --> 40:41.403
We're okay, now.

40:41.939 --> 40:43.803
Mom's gonna be okay.

40:43.828 --> 40:45.883
Can you believe it was the mushrooms?

40:45.908 --> 40:48.037
You stayed with her all night?

40:48.062 --> 40:50.263
Mushrooms, I know.

40:52.788 --> 40:55.420
- I'm glad you're okay.
- Your stitches should come out.

40:55.445 --> 40:59.560
I love you guys. I
love you guys so much.

41:07.924 --> 41:10.409
Both my parents were doctors.

41:14.183 --> 41:16.425
It was all I was ever going to be.

41:20.744 --> 41:22.605
I lost them in the war.

41:24.306 --> 41:26.597
And that's why I don't talk about it.

41:29.815 --> 41:31.863
The scars will fade.

42:08.356 --> 42:10.110
Dr. Hamed?

42:10.791 --> 42:12.158
Detective Greggs.

42:12.263 --> 42:13.635
I'm sorry to bother you at work.

42:13.660 --> 42:15.930
- I know you have a lot on your plate.
- Mm-hmm.

42:15.955 --> 42:18.822
You were involved in a major vehicle
incident a couple of weeks ago?

42:18.847 --> 42:19.867
Mm-hmm.

42:19.892 --> 42:21.954
I'd like to ask you a few
questions about that.

42:21.979 --> 42:24.188
Uh, but I already spoke to the police.

42:24.213 --> 42:26.480
Uh, I'm here about
your former colleague.

42:26.785 --> 42:28.687
Khaled Abdullah.

42:29.400 --> 42:31.400
Emergency personnel took his name,

42:31.425 --> 42:32.752
but then lost track of him

42:32.777 --> 42:34.650
when he fled the scene of the accident.

42:35.112 --> 42:36.751
Do you know where he is?

42:37.814 --> 42:41.748
Mr. Abdullah is wanted for
an immigration violation.

42:42.248 --> 42:44.248
I need to locate him, so...

42:44.646 --> 42:47.891
if you see him, call me.

